This Job launches the iperf command.

Required Arguments:
  type : you have to specify if you want to launch a server (-s) or a client (-c). In the client case, you have also to specify the destination IP (i.e. the server IP)

Optionnal Arguments:
  all the arguments taken by the iperf command

Statistics: it doesn't produce any statistic

Example:
  - Launch an iperf server : -a "mode -s"
  - Launch an iperf client that will connect with the server in 172.20.0.83 : -a "mode -c 172.20.0.83" 

